version_description: My version has different chords than the other ones do and it's in a different key.
My version has more accurate chords in all sections of the song and I've included a strum pattern that very closely matches the original.
This is the exact guitar part, I worked on it with my guitar teacher
Different chords and more accurate chords.
G-minor is an ugly key for guitar, especially if you want to do all first-position (open) chords, so if you want to do that, simply transpose (-3) and use Capo III. The first chord should be Em.
There are errors in all the other versions to many to just correct in the comment section
Edited chord progression, added previously omitted chord changes, and fixed timing (as indicated by spacing) between the lyrics and their corresponding chords. More complex, but more accurate.

song_name: Picture Of My Cck On Your Computer
